<p>Vincent C. Müller, professor of philosophy and ethics of AI and director of the Centre for Philosophy and AI Research at the Friedrich-Alexander-<wbr />Universität Erlangen-Nürnberg, is the winner of the 2025 Covey Award.<span id="more-53260"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class=" wp-image-53261 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/muller-vincent-photo.jpg" alt="" width="641" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/muller-vincent-photo.jpg 753w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/muller-vincent-photo-300x187.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/muller-vincent-photo-400x250.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 641px) 100vw, 641px" /></p>
<p>The Covey Award is bestowed by the <a href="https://www.iacap.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">International Association for Computing and Philosophy </a>(IACAP). It  &#8220;recognizes senior scholars with a substantial record of innovative research in the field of computing and philosophy broadly conceived.&#8221;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.sophia.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dr. Müller</a> was selected for the prize owing to his work on &#8220;philosophical problems connected to artificial intelligence, both from an ethical and a theoretical perspective,&#8221; according to the prize announcement, as well as his leadership in the field: he is president of the <a href="https://www.esscs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">European Society for Cognitive Systems</a>, chair and co-founder of the <a href="https://philai.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Society for the Philosophy of Artificial Intelligence</a>, chair of the <a href="https://www.pt-ai.org/tg-els/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">euRobotics topics group on ethical, legal and socio-economic issues</a>, and co-editor of <a href="https://journals.ub.uni-koeln.de/index.php/phai" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Philosophy of AI</em></a>. A book of his, <i>Can Machines Think? Fundamental Problems of Artificial Intelligence</i><em>, </em>is forthcoming from Oxford University Press. You can learn more about his writings <a href="http://www.sophia.de/publications.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>He will deliver the Covey Award Keynote Address at the IACAP 2025 conference taking place at the University of Twente in July.</p>
<p>The Covey Award is named for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preston_Covey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Preston Covey</a> (1942-2006), a philosopher known for bringing computing and philosophy together.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/04/02/muller-wins-covey-award/">Müller Wins Covey Award</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>